# Design System — PXV Brand

## Colors (CSS variables in globals.css)
- `primary` (#0E56FA) — Main brand blue, CTAs, links
- `secondary` (#17CAFA) — Accent cyan, gradients
- `pxv-dark` (#01001F) — Dark backgrounds, text
- `pxv-light` — Light backgrounds
- `accent` — Blend of primary/secondary

## Typography
- SF Pro Display — body/default font
- Plus Jakarta Sans — headings, emphasis
- Weights: 300–800

## Gradients & Animations
- `gradient-text` — primary → accent → secondary text gradient
- `animate-gradient-x` — horizontal gradient animation
- `animate-float` — floating decorative elements
- Use Framer Motion for scroll-triggered and view-based animations
- Use Tailwind keyframes (`animate-*`) for simple repeating effects

## Styling Rules
- Always use Tailwind utility classes
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Use `hsl(var(--token))` for brand colors in custom CSS
- Border radius: use `rounded-lg`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-sm` (mapped to --radius)
- Responsive: mobile-first (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints)

# Component Priority

1. `components/ui/` (shadcn primitives) — Button, Card, Input, Label, Textarea
2. `components/` (custom) — Navbar, Header, Hero, Form, TeamMemberCard
3. Native HTML elements — only when no component fits

Always use `@/` path alias for imports.

# Key Patterns

- Client components: add `"use client"` directive at top
- Animation: wrap with `<motion.div>` from Framer Motion
- Forms: use controlled components with React state
- API integration: use Next.js Route Handlers in `app/api/`
- Toast notifications: use `toast` from `sonner`

